      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:36:13",
      "text": [
        " تُقْطَعُ يَدُ السَّارِقِ وَ يُتْرَكُ إِبْهَامُهُ وَ صَدْرُ رَاحَتِهِ وَ تُقْطَعُ رِجْلُهُ وَ تُتْرَكُ لَهُ عَقِبُهُ يَمْشِي عَلَيْهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Jabbar, from Safwan, from Is’haq Bin Ammar, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ibrahim<sup>asws</sup> (7<sup>th</sup> Imam<sup>asws</sup>) having said: ‘The hand of the thief would be cut and his thumb would be left alone along with the centre of the palm; and his leg would be cut and his sole would be left alone so he can walk upon it’."
        ]
      }
